July 24 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Bell Aliant Inc and Linamar, on Thursday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Bell Aliant Inc <BA.TO>: CIBC, Canaccord Genuity raise target price  * Rubicon Minerals Corp <RMX.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from speculative buy   Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Thursday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Altus Group Ltd <AIF.TO>: BMO raises target price to C$27 from C$24; rating outperform  * BCE <BCE.TO>: National Bank Financial raises target price to C$51.50  * BCE <BCE.TO>: TD Securities raises target price to C$49 from C$48; rating hold  * Bell Aliant Inc <BA.TO>: CIBC raises target price to C$31 from C$27; sector performer  * Bell Aliant Inc <BA.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$31 from C$26; hold  * Bell Aliant Inc <BA.TO>: TD Securities cuts to tender from hold  * Bell Aliant Inc <BA.TO>: TD Securities raises target price to C$31 from C$27.00  * Bell Canada Enterprises <BCE.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$49 from C$48; hold  * Ithaca Energy <IAE.TO>: Imperial Capital raises target to C$3.30 from C$3.15; outperform  * Linamar <LNR.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price by C$1 to C$58  * Lucara Diamond <LUC.TO>: RBC raises price target to C$3; rating sector perform  * Maple Leaf Foods Inc <MFI.TO>: RBC raises target price to C$21 from C$18; sector perform  * Rubicon Minerals Corp <RMX.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from speculative buy